Check 2: Are duplicates coming from same member having multiple emails on same update date?

This is very important.

SELECT
    ED.MBI,
    EE.ENTITY_ID,
    EE.UPDATEDATE,
    COUNT(*) AS ROW_COUNT,
    COUNT(DISTINCT EE.EMAILADDRESS) AS DISTINCT_EMAIL_COUNT
FROM LIG_PRD_MRCS_OH_OUTREACH_SH_DB.MRCS_OH_OUTREACH.TBL_CONTACT_EMAIL EE
INNER JOIN LIG_PRD_MRCS_OH_OUTREACH_SH_DB.MRCS_OH_OUTREACH.TBL_DEMOGRAPHIC ED
    ON EE.ENTITY_ID = ED.ENTITY_ID
GROUP BY
    ED.MBI,
    EE.ENTITY_ID,
    EE.UPDATEDATE
HAVING COUNT(*) > 1
ORDER BY ROW_COUNT DESC;

This tells you whether the same member/entity has multiple rows with the same update date.

