One important improvement you may want to mention

Right now, your logic can still return multiple rows if a member has:

multiple valid email addresses
same max UPDATEDATE

A cleaner approach is often to use ROW_NUMBER() and explicitly pick one row.

Example pattern:

QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
    PARTITION BY ED.MBI
    ORDER BY EE.UPDATEDATE DESC, EE.EMAILADDRESS
) = 1

This is better than relying on MAX_UPDATE_DATE + DISTINCT.

Your director may like that.

One more thing to review: NOT IN

This part:

EE.ENTITY_ID NOT IN (
    SELECT DISTINCT ENTITY_ID
    FROM ...TBL_CONSENT_DNC
    ...
)

can behave unexpectedly if the subquery contains NULL.

Safer version is usually NOT EXISTS.

Example:

AND NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1
    FROM LIG_PRD_MRCS_OH_OUTREACH_SH_DB.MRCS_OH_OUTREACH.TBL_CONSENT_DNC DNE
    WHERE DNE.ENTITY_ID = EE.ENTITY_ID
      AND UPPER(DNE.PREF_CODE) = 'DO_NOT_EMAIL'
      AND UPPER(DNE.SELECTED) = 'Y'
)

That is another good review point.

